Welcome to Know Your Rights,Know Your Rights,Select an area below to find out more about your rights.,What best describes your situation?,Click on the questions below to expand answers.,Back,NA,I've been arrested,How can I pay bail during COVID-19?,"On April 6, the Judicial Council of California adopted 11 Emergency Rules and established that bail for infractions will be set at $0.00, while bail for technical violations of felony probation, Post Release Community Supervision (PRCS), or parole will be set at $5,000.00. The rules are repealed on June 10, but counties like Alameda have adopted their own “zero bail” emergency bail schedule."
